The paper discusses the calibration of parameters in agent-based models, which falls under the category of multi-agent systems (MAS) and machine learning. Therefore, cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are the most likely categories. The paper also discusses the use of simulations in various domains, such as urban growth modeling and market dynamics modeling, which falls under the category of computational engineering (cs.CE). The paper also discusses the use of digital twin, which is a concept related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
